
`xinit` starts the → Linux/X/index[X Server].

On systems that are not using a → Linux/X/display-manager, `xinit` also starts a first program.

When not otherwise instructed, `xinit` reads → Linux/fhs/home/username/_xinitrc

{ .xinitrc

  When `xinit` is started without stating the client program, xinit will execute → Linux/fhs/home/username/_xinitrc.

}

sa:
  A »front end« to xinit is the → Linux/X/startx[`startx`] script.

  → Linux/X/xserverrc,
  → Linux/X/xinitrc
